article.headline: Montana State defeats UMKC 74-62
article.description: — Max Agbonkpolo's 17 points helped Montana State defeat Kansas City 74-62 on Saturday night.

article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. -- — Max Agbonkpolo's 17 points helped Montana State defeat Kansas City 74-62 on Saturday night. Agbonkpolo also contributed nine rebounds for the Bobcats (5-5). Brandon Walker added 16 points while going 6 of 10 and 3 of 8 from the free-throw line and five rebounds. Brian Goracke had 15 points and shot 4 for 11 (3 for 7 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free-throw line. The Kangaroos (4-7) were led by Davontae Hall, who recorded 18 points and three steals. UMKC also got eight points from Jamar Brown and Melvyn Ebonkoli. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
